OL,4,CSex abuse victim's shock at seeing
OL,5,Cattacker back in community
OL,6, A victim of sexual abuse has said she
OL,7, cannot heal with her attacker now
OL,8, living back in her community.
OL,10,FDespite being told she would not see
OL,11,Fthe man when he left prison because he
OL,12,Fwas housebound due to his poor health,
OL,13,FLeah Walker was "devastated" when she
OL,14,Fbumped into him at a supermarket.
OL,16,F"I was reassured I wouldn't see my
OL,17,Fabuser - then I saw him in Sainsbury's
OL,18,Fand it shook me to my core," she said.
OL,20,FThe Probation Service has apologised
OL,21,Fand said it has taken immediate action.
